foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, Census reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2014, as “23.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to 1 request that was closed in FY2014, which was reopened and fulfilled in FY2015. The correct number is “24.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2015 for Census has been amended to “24” in the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, ITA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2014 as “74.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to ITA determining in FY2015 that 1 pending Privacy Act request from FY2014 must also be processed under the FOIA. The correct number is “75.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2015 for ITA has been amended to “75” in the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, NTIS reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2014 as “1.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “2” requests is due to 2 requests pending from FY 2014 but not reported, which were fulfilled in FY 2015. The correct number is “3.” Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2015 for NTIS has been amended to “3” in the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests pending at the end of FY2014 was reported as “486.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests pending as of the start of FY2015 for Census, ITA, and NTIS (see footnotes above), the agency overall number of requests pending as of the start of FY2015 has been amended to “490.”

foia:BacklogSection.foia:FootnoteText: AGC/Admin processes the appeals for all the Department of Commerce components, except for PTO. Data provided by AGC/Admin.
AGC/Admin processed the appeals for OIG prior to November 19, 2014. Any backlogged appeals for OIG prior to November 19 are being processed by AGC/Admin.
OIG began processing its own appeals on November 19, 2014. Any backlogged appeals for OIG after November 19 were reported by OIG.

foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, ITA reported “26” consultations pending as of the end of the Fiscal Year. This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “6” consultations is due to 6 consultations being reported incorrectly as referrals in FY 2014. The correct number is “32.” Therefore, the number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2014 for ITA has been amended to “32” in the FY2015 Annual FOIA Report.

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of consultations pending at the end of FY2014 was reported as “27.” Due to the amendment in the number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2015 for ITA (see footnote above), the agency overall number of consultations pending as of the start of FY2015 has been amended to “33.”

foia:ProcessedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, Census reported the number of requests processed during the Fiscal Year as “401.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to 1 request that was closed in FY2014, which was reopened and fulfilled in FY2015. Therefore, the number of requests processed as of the end of FY2014 for Census was actually “400.”

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, ITA reported the number of requests processed during the Fiscal Year as “21.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to ITA determining in FY2015 that 1 Privacy Act request from FY2014 must also be processed under the FOIA. Therefore, the number of requests processed as of the end of FY2014 for ITA was actually “20.”

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests processed during the Fiscal Year as “1776.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests processed for Census and ITA in FY2014 (see footnotes above), the agency overall number of requests processed during FY2014 for the agency overall was actually “1774.”

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: In the FY204 Annual FOIA Report, Census reported the number of requests backlogged at the end of FY 2014 as “2.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to a request fulfilled in FY 2014, but not documented until FY2015. Therefore, the number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2014 for Census was actually “1.”

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, PTO reported the number of requests backlogged at the end of FY 204 as “2.” This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of “1” request is due to a request fulfilled in FY 2014, but not documented until FY2015. Therefore, the number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2014 for PTO was actually “1.”

In the FY2014 Annual FOIA Report, the agency overall number of requests backlogged at the end of FY2014 was reported as “362.” Due to the amendment in the number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2014 for Census and PTO (see footnote above), the agency overall number of requests backlogged as of the end of FY2014 for the agency overall was actually “360.”

foia:ProcessedAppealComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: On November 19, 2014, OIG began processing its own appeals. OIG appeals received before November 19, 2014 were processed by AGC/Admin and are reflected in the AGC/Admin figures in the FY2015 Report.

foia:BackloggedAppealComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: Last fiscal year, appeals were listed by the component that processed the initial determination, not the component that processed the appeal in DOC’s FY 14 Annual Report. Since AGC/Admin processes the appeals for all of the Department of Commerce, except for OIG and PTO, appeals for the components are listed under AGC/Admin for the FY 15 Annual Report.
